          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832076?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">哥伦比亚毒贩戴罗·安东尼奥·乌苏加·大卫去年被哥伦比亚引渡到美国。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：哥伦比亚国家警察/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119886"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-fanelli" itemprop="url" rel="author">詹姆斯·法内利</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 4:39 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-drug-kingpin-sentenced-to-45-years-in-u-s-prison-4a78fe96"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>一名曾经是该国头号通缉犯之一的哥伦比亚毒枭周二在布鲁克林联邦法院被判处 45 年监禁，罪名是监督将 100 多吨可卡因走私到中美洲和美国。</p><p> 51 岁的戴罗·安东尼奥·乌苏加·大卫 (Dairo Antonio Úsuga David) <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-drug-kingpin-pleads-guilty-to-smuggling-cocaine-into-u-s-11674682175?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一月份承认经营犯罪企业和另外两项与毒品有关的指控</a>，他当时告诉联邦法官，他“从贩毒活动中获得了大量收入和资源”。认罪协议解决了乌苏加·大卫面临的三项联邦起诉。</p><p>美国地区法官多拉·利泽特·伊里扎里 (Dora Lizette Irizarry) 判处 45 年监禁，与布鲁克林美国检察官办公室联邦检察官所寻求的刑期一致。</p><p>检察官在宣判前的一份法庭文件中表示，近十年来，乌苏加·大卫一直是海湾部落的领导人，该部落是一个由至少 1000 名战士组成的农村民兵组织，在哥伦比亚多个省份开展活动。检察官称，乌苏加·大卫在位期间监督毒品贩运，同时恐吓社区。</p><p>检察官在文件中写道：“他下令杀害、绑架和折磨竞争对手，以及他认为配合执法部门侵犯他个人利益的个人。”</p><p>乌苏加·大卫 (Úsuga David) 的律师请求判处 25 年监禁，并在一份法庭文件中表示，法官应该考虑到他们当事人的童年受到暴力和贫困的影响。</p><p> “先生。乌苏加在贫困的环境中长大，几乎没有晋升的机会，自相残杀的暴力不断，哥伦比亚国家在日常生活的最基本方面明显缺位，”律师们说。</p><p>乌苏加·大卫的律师没有立即回应置评请求。</p><p>乌苏加·大卫 (Úsuga David) 又名奥托尼尔 (Otoniel)，经过大规模搜捕<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-drug-trafficking-kingpin-otoniel-captured-was-wanted-by-u-s-11635091770?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，于 2021 年在哥伦比亚和巴拿马边境附近的一个藏身处被捕</a>。</p><p>联邦调查人员多年来一直追捕他，美国悬赏 500 万美元寻找导致他被捕的信息。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/suspected-colombian-drug-kingpin-extradited-to-u-s-11651787114?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">他去年被引渡到美国</a>。</p><p>写信给 James Fanelli： <a href="mailto:james.fanelli@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">james.fanelli@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 20:39:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-drug-kingpin-sentenced-to-45-years-in-us-prison-4a78fe96</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombian-drug-kingpin-sentenced-to-45-years-in-us-prison-4a78fe96<author><![CDATA[James Fanelli]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Niger Junta Snubs U.S.-Backed Peace Mission]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>政变领导人拒绝欢迎旨在讨论回归文官政府的代表团，增加了地区战争的风险<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119036"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="560" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831613?width=860&amp;height=560" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">和平使团原定于周二抵达尼日尔首都尼亚美。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119036"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/drew-hinshaw" itemprop="url" rel="author">德鲁·欣肖</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-faucon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伯努瓦·福孔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 3:12（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-junta-snubs-u-s-backed-peace-mission-a79f76e5"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>尼日尔新军政府周二拒绝允许美国支持的和平使团从邻国尼日利亚出发访问，称无法保证他们在首都的安全，首都的道路现在被民族主义青年封锁。</p><p>军政府对其他西非政府派出的代表团的冷落加剧了西非沿海文职政府与该地区内陆军事政权之间爆发战争的风险。</p><p>由尼日利亚前国家元首率领的代表团原定于周二抵达尼日尔首都尼亚美，距该国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">总统卫队夺权</a>两周后。在那里，他们希望说服军政府领导人采取措施<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-leaders-detain-ministers-party-officials-6ba1efa1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">恢复文官统治</a>，并防止与非洲人口最多的邻国尼日利亚<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/france-prepares-to-evacuate-european-citizens-from-coup-hit-niger-d46774af?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">发生武装冲突的风险</a>。</p><p>尼日利亚在西非国家经济共同体其他 10 个文职政府的支持下，威胁称，如果军政府领导人不下台，将使用武力推翻军政府。周四，尼日利亚将主办西非总统和外交部长紧急会议，讨论下一步行动。</p><p>尼日尔外交部表示，公众对尼日利亚试图扭转政变的愤怒将危及代表团的安全。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="480" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831650?width=700&amp;height=480" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一些尼日尔人对尼亚美军事政变表示支持。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>过去几天，成群的年轻人在连接尼亚美机场和首都的道路上以及通往总统府的大道上设置了路障，搜查汽车，并发誓要保卫国家。反对政变的居民表示，他们害怕抗议或表达自己的观点。</p><p> “我们这里有数百人 24 小时守卫，”在尼亚美中部守卫路障的支持政变武装分子易卜拉欣·纳迈瓦 (Ibrahim Namaiwa) 说。 “任何对士兵发动战争的人都必须先杀死我们。”</p><p>周一，尼日尔军政府欢迎来自布基纳法索和马里军事政权的代表团，这两个与莫斯科结盟的邻国誓言保卫尼日尔免受西非国家区域联盟西非经共体的干预。俄罗斯公开反对对尼日尔进行武装干预，其瓦格纳雇佣军组织表示愿意帮助军政府自卫。</p><p>瓦格纳领导人叶夫根尼·普里戈任（Yevgeny Prigozhin）在针对尼日尔新军政府领导人的音频消息中说：“请随时给我们打电话。”该消息于周二在与该组织相关的 Telegram 频道上分享。</p><p>支持西非经共体和平使命的美国在尼日尔拥有约 1,100 名士兵和数个无人机基地，直到上个月政变之前，尼日尔一直是美国在撒哈拉地区的顶级反恐伙伴。美国已花费约 5 亿美元建设尼日尔军队，其中包括价值 1.1 亿美元的阿加德兹无人机基地。</p><p>美国已与至少一名军政府高级成员进行会谈，以说服政变领导人回归民主统治。周一，代理副国务卿维多利亚·纽兰前往尼日尔会见军政府，试图通过外交手段解决紧张局势。</p><p> “这些谈话非常坦诚，有时也相当困难，”她告诉记者。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831616?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">西非国家和西方政府实施的金融制裁开始产生影响。尼亚美的一个市场。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>周二，尼日利亚官员试图压制有关军事干预的言论，但他们表示军事干预仍然是西非经共体的最后手段。</p><p>尼日利亚总统发言人阿朱里·恩格拉莱 (Ajuri Ngelale) 表示：“虽然西非经共体的谈判桌上没有任何选项，但没有任何投机性的猜测可以阻止正在进行的调解努力，以实现尼日尔共和国和平恢复民主统治。”</p><p>尼日利亚的文官政府——与塞内加尔、科特迪瓦和其他西非民主国家的文官政府一样——担心未能扭转尼日尔的政变将激励其他国家的军官夺取政权。就在过去三年里，马里发生了两次政变，布基纳法索又发生了两次政变，几内亚发生了一次，乍得又发生了一次。</p><p>更广泛地说，这个拥有 4.41 亿人口的地区正面临着青年人普遍失业、城市拥挤以及对未来繁荣的悲观预期的浪潮。基地组织和伊斯兰国盟友叛乱分子还在马里、布基纳法索以及尼日利亚和尼日尔发动了数千次袭击。</p><p>具有超凡魅力的军事统治者将自己视为技术官僚和亲西方文职政府的有吸引力的替代方案。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-us-russia-africa-86cf1454?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">俄罗斯也填补了这一空缺</a>，为那些认为自己没有从与巴黎长达一个世纪的经济和政治关系中受益的前法国殖民地提供了自己的反殖民伙伴关系。</p><p>一些尼亚美居民表示，虽然他们最初并不支持政变，但他们认为军事统治比旨在恢复民主的武装冲突更好。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=7F7AB6E6-CE60-46D3-B0B7-C075C1006060&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fniger-junta-snubs-u-s-backed-peace-mission-a79f76e5&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">尼日尔政变领导人宣布关闭其领空，导致全国各地的航班改道。与此同时，其他西非国家为军政府设定的周日最后期限已经过去。照片：Flightradar24.com<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>“我没有呼吁发动政变，但既然政变已经发生，就应该允许尼日尔人民在不受外界干扰的情况下解决问题，”进口商奥马鲁·马拉姆·伊萨 (Umaru Malam Isa) 表示。 “虽然我不喜欢政变，但这可能是尼日尔实现发展的唯一途径。”</p><p>与此同时，政变的反对者表示，一波对政治领导人盟友的逮捕浪潮以及对最初的民主抗议活动的暴力镇压使他们无法发声，尽管西非经共体和西方政府实施的贸易和金融制裁已开始咬。尼亚美的一名医生表示，军政府冻结了除水电以外的其他支出，他担心药物很快就会耗尽。</p><p> “像我这样反对政变的人都不敢表达自己的观点，”医生说。 “只有一侧携带武器。”</p><p>写信给 Drew Hinshaw ( <a href="mailto:drew.hinshaw@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">drew.hinshaw@wsj.com)</a>和 Benoit Faucon ( <a href="mailto:benoit.faucon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.faucon@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 19:12:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-junta-snubs-us-backed-peace-mission-a79f76e5</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-junta-snubs-us-backed-peace-mission-a79f76e5<author><![CDATA[Drew HinshawBenoit Faucon]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>叛乱</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>叛乱</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Latin American Countries Aim to Curb Amazon Deforestation]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>巴西总统接待地区领导人，因为雨林面临失去帮助抵消气候变化能力的风险<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831814/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="长期以来，亚马逊雨林吸收的碳多于释放的碳，但近 20% 的原始森林现已消失。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>长期以来，亚马逊雨林吸收的碳多于释放的碳，但近 20% 的原始森林现已消失。 UESLEI MARCELINO/路透社<span>UESLEI MARCELINO/路透社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119095"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119095"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/samantha-pearson" itemprop="url" rel="author">萨曼莎·皮尔森</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/luciana-magalhaes" itemprop="url" rel="author">卢西亚娜·马加哈斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 1:38 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/latin-american-countries-aim-to-curb-amazon-deforestation-c479cfd5"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>圣保罗——共享亚马逊雨林的拉丁美洲国家周二在巴西丛林城市贝伦举行了为期两天的会议，旨在制止<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazonian-destruction-risesbefore-brazil-presidential-election-11663166106?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">森林砍伐</a>，许多科学家指责森林砍伐加速了气候变化。</p><p>巴西拥有<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazil-battles-for-amazon-tribe-known-as-guardian-of-the-rainforest-5a66569d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">世界上 60% 的最大雨林</a>，该国为亚马逊其他地区的国家（秘鲁、哥伦比亚、玻利维亚、委内瑞拉、厄瓜多尔、圭亚那和苏里南）的总统和高级官员举行了会议。此次峰会是亚马逊合作条约组织 14 年来的首次峰会，该组织源于 1978 年亚马逊国家签署的一项条约，旨在促进该地区的和谐发展。法国驻巴西利亚大使代表法国负责管理南美洲东北部的法属圭亚那。</p><p>此次会议召开之际，巴西总统路易斯·伊纳西奥·卢拉·达席尔瓦寻求通过这项已有 45 年历史的条约，将巴西定位为全球反对森林砍伐的主要声音，并成为非洲大陆跨境环境合作的推动者。</p><p> “恢复和扩大这种合作从未如此紧迫——这是我们时代的挑战，”达席尔瓦在周二的开幕致辞中说。</p><p>其他拥有大片热带森林的国家，如印度尼西亚、刚果共和国和刚果民主共和国，预计将与挪威和德国一起参加会议，这些国家为毁林计划做出了贡献。今年将在迪拜主办<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-a-e-names-oil-chief-to-run-cop28-climate-summit-11673542016?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">联合国气候峰会的</a>阿拉伯联合酋长国也将出席。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831850?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">巴西总统路易斯·伊纳西奥·卢拉·达席尔瓦在贝伦峰会上。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：安东尼奥·拉塞尔达/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>亚马逊雨林的面积是印度的两倍，长期以来吸收的碳多于释放的碳，成为全球气候变化的重要制动因素。但随着近 20% 的原始森林消失，追踪森林的科学家表示，亚马逊可能已经接近所谓的不可逆转的临界点，届时它将变得干燥，最终变成稀树草原。影响可能是全球性的。气候科学家将森林丧失归咎于全球变暖，美国环境保护署表示，这解释了为什么热浪在美国等国家变得越来越普遍。</p><p>巴西国家空间研究所的初步数据显示，巴西亚马逊地区的森林砍伐达到自达席尔瓦一月上任以来四年来的最低水平，今年前六个月与去年同期相比下降了约34%研究，称为INPE。尽管达席尔瓦发誓要到 2030 年将丛林破坏降至零，但他认为，这一目标不能以牺牲巴西亚马逊地区约 3000 万居民的生计为代价。</p><p>达席尔瓦认为，巴西必须利用国外的融资和投资在亚马逊地区建立新的绿色经济，并发展受监管的碳市场。巴西依靠外国捐款来帮助其资金不足的环境执法机构运作，这些机构使用直升机、无人机和其他设备来监测广大地区的非法森林砍伐。</p><p>达席尔瓦在一份政府声明中表示：“我们想要告诉世界我们将如何处理我们的森林，以及世界必须采取哪些措施来帮助我们。”达席尔瓦表示，他计划向富裕国家施压，要求它们履行在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/final-draft-of-global-climate-change-deal-is-complete-1449906731?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2015年巴黎气候协议</a>中做出的承诺，每年提供1000亿美元帮助发展中国家应对气候变化。</p><p>包括哥伦比亚和秘鲁在内的其他拉丁美洲国家也制定了森林砍伐目标，但面临着非法采矿和贩毒团伙的严重挑战，这些团伙加强了对森林的控制，联合国最近将其称为“毒品森林砍伐”。</p><p>科学家表示，解决森林砍伐问题是南美洲面临的最紧迫任务之一。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831817?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名巴西官员在检查巴西普拉卡斯的一家锯木厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：UESLEI MARCELINO/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831819?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">巴西依靠外国捐款来帮助其资金不足的环境执法机构运作。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的托马索·普罗蒂</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>INPE 研究员 Luciana Gatti 在 2021 年发表的一项研究显示，亚马逊东南部地区森林砍伐严重的地区已经不再发挥碳吸收器的作用，而是成为碳源。INPE 使用卫星跟踪森林砍伐情况。</p><p>丹尼尔·内普斯塔德说，亚马逊雨林影响着世界各地的天气模式，随着森林砍伐的加剧，这可能会使极端天气事件变得更加普遍。</p>他是加州地球创新研究所的负责人，在亚马逊工作了 30 多年。<p></p><p>内普斯塔德说：“森林是一个全球空调装置……一个影响世界各地天气的巨大热处理机器。”他补充说，所有领导人愿意开会讨论这个问题本身就是一个“非常积极的成果”。</p><p>今年， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/extreme-heat-waves-across-the-world-photos-7cc1544d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">致命的热浪</a>扰乱了美国、欧洲和亚洲大部分地区的日常生活，而南美洲冬季异常高温导致安第斯山脉的积雪融化。</p><p>环保人士表示，区域协调至关重要。在亚马逊深处，土著社区经常跨越边界，伐木者和犯罪团伙可以自由活动，一国的努力很容易因邻国的努力而变得无效。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>是否采取了足够的措施来制止亚马逊地区的森林砍伐？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>就在一年前，当达席尔瓦的右翼前任</p>贾尔·博尔索纳罗担任总统。博尔索纳罗开玩笑地称自己为“电锯船长”，他削减了环境执法资金，并对外国试图影响他对亚马逊的管理工作感到愤怒，尽管他呼吁外国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazils-climate-overture-to-biden-pay-us-not-to-raze-amazon-11618997400?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">为砍伐森林活动提供资金</a>。<p></p><p>根据 INPE 的数据，在这位保守派领导人的领导下，四年内，一片比佛蒙特州还大的森林被毁。</p><p>政治学家表示，去年 10 月达席尔瓦的当选将南美大部分地区置于一群松散联盟的左翼领导人手中，从而缓和了有关亚马逊地区问题的区域谈判，而该问题从未产生过切实的合作。</p><p>诚然，参加贝伦峰会的国家之间存在着冲突点。</p><p>虽然达席尔瓦正在考虑开发亚马逊河口附近的海上石油资源，以帮助降低国内燃料成本，但他的哥伦比亚同行古斯塔沃·佩特罗上个月呼吁阻止该地区所有新的石油开发。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831860?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">巴西里约热内卢州一家炼油厂附近的牛群正在吃草。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：佩德罗·普拉多/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“作为国家元首，我们必须确保亚马逊停止新的石油和天然气勘探，” <a href="https://www.miamiherald.com/opinion/op-ed/article277248923.html" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">佩特罗上个月在《迈阿密先驱报》上写道</a>。 “即使我们正在解决国内的基本社会问题，但生活成本危机和猖獗的通货膨胀加剧了这些问题，我们也必须表现出勇气。”</p><p>巴西气候观测站的环保组织联盟负责人马西奥·阿斯特里尼表示，亚马逊流域国家可能会在保护土著社区、打击边境犯罪以及支持科学研究以更好地了解森林方面找到共同点。</p><p> “这些国家处于不同的政治局势……但他们都在议程中找到了同意这一点的空间，并聚在一起讨论这些敏感问题，”阿斯特里尼说。</p><p>不过，阿斯特里尼说，他们最大的共同点是希望让更富裕的国家帮助支付所有这些费用。</p><p> “给我钱——这是他们都会异口同声地说的一件事，”他说。</p><p>写信给 Samantha Pearson（ <a href="mailto:samantha.pearson@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">samantha.pearson@wsj.com）</a>和 Luciana Magalhaes（ <a href="mailto:luciana.magalhaes@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">luciana.magalhaes@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:38:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/latin-american-countries-aim-to-curb-amazon-deforestation-c479cfd5</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/latin-american-countries-aim-to-curb-amazon-deforestation-c479cfd5<author><![CDATA[Samantha PearsonLuciana Magalhaes]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>森林砍伐</category><category>全球/世界问题</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>卢西安娜·加蒂</category><category>丹尼尔·内普斯塔德</category><category>贾尔·博尔索纳罗</category><category>古斯塔沃·佩特罗</category><category>马西奥·阿斯特里尼</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>砍伐森林</category><category>全球的</category><category>世界问题</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese Exports Fall at Steepest Pace Since February 2020]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>尽管对俄罗斯的出口蓬勃发展，但出境货运量的下滑反映了与西方世界的贸易关系的恶化<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117715"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="615" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831432?width=860&amp;height=615" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 7月份中国对美国和欧盟的出口分别下降了20%以上。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117715"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stella-yifan-xie" itemprop="url" rel="author">谢一凡</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 8 日下午 1:16（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>香港——7月份中国对世界其他地区的出口大幅下滑，加剧了世界第二大经济体面临的挑战，并提供了新的证据表明西方需求枯竭正在损害北京<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-fading-recovery-tests-policy-makers-economic-playbook-8ce334f9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">重振经济增长的努力</a>。</p><p>经过春季短暂的反弹后，中国的商品出口恢复了自去年10月以来的长期下滑，当时西方发达国家的消费者开始将支出从购买家具和电子产品转向购买家具和电子产品。娱乐和外出就餐等服务。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-and-china-sent-large-naval-patrol-near-alaska-127de28b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">北京与以美国为首的西方国家之间不断恶化的地缘政治紧张局势</a>也促使一些西方制造商减少对中国供应链的依赖，预计这将削弱两国之间的贸易关系。</p><p>最近的数据表明中国经济的问题日益严重。该国陷入困境的房地产市场本周出现了新的困境迹象。青年失业率创历史新高。最新数据显示，中国正处于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/while-everyone-else-fights-inflation-chinas-deflation-fears-deepen-4045cabf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">陷入通货紧缩的边缘</a>，许多人担心这种情况可能会将经济拖入螺旋式下降。</p><p>亚洲其他出口大国也在努力应对全球贸易需求的下滑。韩国 7 月份出口同比下降 16.5%，降幅较 6 月份扩大。采购经理人指数显示，上个月七个亚洲国家中有五个国家的制造业出现收缩，其中包括中国和越南，这表明西方的潜在需求疲软。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>总而言之，中国和亚洲其他地区的低迷数据表明，全球增长放缓的影响开始更加严重。</p><p>经济学家预测，由于经济衰退的威胁依然存在，美国和欧洲的增长阻力（部分原因是持续的通胀压力）将在今年剩余时间内继续抑制消费者支出和企业借贷。</p><p>联合国贸易和发展会议在 6 月的一份报告中写道：“总体而言，2023 年下半年全球贸易前景悲观。”</p><p>该组织目前预测，受通胀和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰战争等</a>一系列因素影响，全球货物贸易在今年前三个月增长1.9%后，第二季度将环比萎缩0.4% <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">。</a></p><p>中国海关总署周二发布的数据显示，7 月份来自中国的海外发货量同比下降 14.5%，这是自 2020 年 2 月（Covid-19 大流行初期）以来的最大同比降幅。</p><p>与去年同期相比，上个月中国对美国和欧盟的出口均下降了20%以上。有一个唯一的亮点：海关数据计算显示，7 月份中国对俄罗斯的出口量猛增。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831448?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国消费者正在勒紧裤腰带，给中国经济复苏带来压力。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Ng Hanguan/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>对中国来说，出口疲软意味着其国内经济面临更多麻烦，国内经济<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-barely-grows-as-recovery-fades-5652a92a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">在多个方面都陷入困境</a>。该国的经济复苏是由去年底取消新冠疫情控制措施引发的，但自四月份以来一直在失去动力。</p><p>经济学家表示，私营部门多年来一直受到Covid-19限制和监管打压的打击，消费者信心疲软导致他们避免在从公寓到家用电器的大件商品上挥霍。</p><p>在经历了年初的短暂反弹之后，今年中国的房地产市场进一步恶化。作为主要增长动力的房地产行业投资今年前六个月同比下降 8%，抑制了中国对大宗商品的需求。</p><p>周一，<span class="company-name-type">被</span>中国当局誉为其他典范的房地产开发商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HK/XHKG/2007" class="">碧桂园控股</a>公司未能支付两只美元债券的利息。</p><p>穆迪分析公司(Moody&#39;s Analytics)首席亚太经济学家史蒂夫·科克伦(Steve Cochrane)表示，7月份低于标准的贸易数据对中国政策制定者及其对第三季度经济加速的希望来说意味着更多坏消息。</p><p> “对于中国来说，回归将是一个漫长的过程，”他说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=E87CB6AE-077A-4221-86C2-EE6981C09C4C&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国生产的玉米比任何其他作物都多，去年美国农场向中国出售了价值 53 亿美元的玉米。但中国多年来一直在吸引其他生产商，并且正在探索实现长期自给自足的方法。插图：赵安妮<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>7月份中国出境货物运输量下降14.5%，降幅大于6月份12.4%的同比降幅，也超出了《华尔街日报》经济学家调查的12%的降幅预期。</p><p> 7月份中国对美国的货物发货量同比下降23%。对欧盟和东南亚国家联盟（包括新加坡和印度尼西亚在内的 10 个国家）的出口量均下降了约 21%。</p><p>另外，由于进出口双双下降，美国与世界其他地区的贸易在 6 月份出现下滑，这是高利率正在给美国经济活动降温的最新迹象。</p><p>美国商务部周二表示，美国 6 月份进口额较上月下降 1%，至经季节性调整后的 3130 亿美元，为 2021 年 11 月以来的最低水平。出口下滑0.1%。</p><p> 6月份美国从中国的商品进口环比下降4.3%。 6月份对华贸易逆差减少21亿美元至228亿美元，对华出口创2021年2月以来最低水平。</p><p>按12个月计算，6月份美国对华贸易逆差降至3131亿美元，为2021年1月以来的最低水平。</p><p>俄罗斯是一个因入侵乌克兰而受到西方制裁的国家，在包括汽车在内的高价值商品销售的推动下，7月份中国对俄罗斯的出口量同比增长了52%。中国海关数据显示，今年前7个月，中国对俄罗斯出口同比猛增73%，尽管中国出口总额下降了5%。</p><p>尽管如此，经济学家表示，鉴于与俄罗斯的贸易关系总体规模仍然相对较小，大约相当于中国与美国贸易总额的三分之一，这两个邻国和地缘政治伙伴之间蓬勃发展的贸易不会扭转长期趋势。中国出口整体放缓。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="524" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831447?width=700&amp;height=524" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">得益于汽车等高价值商品的销售，7月份中国对俄罗斯的出口有所增长。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>对于许多中国制造商和出口商来说，坏消息是西方富裕国家正在减少对中国商品的依赖。美国官员及其欧洲盟友一直在敦促企业将生产从中国转移到可信赖的国家圈子。</p><p>这削弱了中美之间的贸易联系。贸发会议的数据显示，在过去的一年半里，美国对中国的出口市场的重要性相对下降，而美国对中国作为商品供应商的依赖程度则进一步下降。</p><p> 7月份中国进口降幅也超出预期，较去年同期下降12.4%，而6月份的降幅为6.8%，这是自1月份以来同比降幅最严重的一个月，远低于接受调查的经济学家预期的5%降幅。</p><p>分析师表示，中国进口量的下降（其中包括中国公司转化为成品的中间产品）反映了整个全球制造业链的更广泛疲软。它还表明，尽管中国经济已经摆脱与新冠病毒相关的限制超过六个月，但国内消费仍然不温不火。</p><p>经济学家表示，最新的一系列疲软经济数据可能会促使北京考虑采取更多刺激措施。</p><p>凯投宏观(Capital Economics)的经济学家表示，中国官员已经下令地方政府更快地发行债券，为基础设施支出提供资金，此举可能会提振中国对大宗商品的需求，并帮助中国进口在未来几个月重获市场份额。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——Grace Zhu、Harriet Torry 和 Anthony DeBarros 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给谢一凡<a href="mailto:stella.xie@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stella.xie@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 17:16:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b<author><![CDATA[Stella Yifan Xie]]></author><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>贸易数据</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>实物贸易</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>碧桂园控股</category><category>2007.香港</category><category>香港:2007</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>贸易数据</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>实物贸易</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Famous Hippie Freetown Is Ganging Up on Drug Criminals]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>哥本哈根的克里斯蒂安尼亚街区吸引了大批游客和顽固的犯罪分子<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831451/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="哥本哈根克里斯蒂安尼亚的居民动员起来，关闭了名为 Pusher Street 的露天大麻市场。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>哥本哈根克里斯蒂安尼亚的居民动员起来，关闭了名为 Pusher Street 的露天大麻市场。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117853"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117853"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sune-engel-rasmussen" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sune Engel Rasmussen</a></span> |詹纳斯·恩格尔 (Janus Engel) 为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日上午 8:06 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-famous-hippie-freetown-is-ganging-up-on-drug-criminals-6f630367"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>哥本哈根——50 年来，丹麦首都克里斯蒂安尼亚 (Christiania) 是一个无政府主义、自由奔放的公社，因其露天大麻市场而享誉全球，吸引了来自世界各地的游客，同时还有顽固的犯罪分子和警方的定期镇压。</p><p>现在，一群居民奋起反抗控制了该行业的帮派，进行了一次危险的秘密行动，旨在关闭著名的普舍街。</p><p>近年来，有组织的犯罪分子将克里斯蒂安尼亚的大部分居民赶出了利润丰厚的大麻贸易，使北欧最大的旅游景点之一和丹麦宽容的象征变得恶化。</p><p>在发生一系列日益严重的暴力事件（包括几起杀戮）之后，许多居民已经受够了。周二黎明前，大约 50 名基督教徒（公社居民的称呼）在夜深人静时聚集在一起，观看他们订购的起重机使用集装箱和混凝土墙封锁普舍街的入口，几个小时后毒贩就会到达这里。开始一天的工作。</p><p>活动人士表示，“采取这一行动是希望将克里斯蒂安尼亚从帮派和铁杆犯罪分子的暴政中解放出来。”他们补充说，他们这样做是冒着自身安全的巨大风险的。 “我们都是普通人，必须去上班，为孩子们打包饭盒。这些团伙准备使用暴力并杀人，以保护他们的收入和领土。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831475?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">克里斯蒂安尼亚的许多居民担心封锁街道行动后几天内毒贩的报复。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>克里斯蒂安尼亚的居民和毒贩之间的对决是丹麦和欧洲毒品市场<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-peaceful-sweden-became-europes-gun-murder-capital-a5b500a7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">日益扩大和暴力</a>的结果。这也标志着欧洲最激进、最持久的社会实验之一的转折点，该实验自 1971 年成立以来一直在违反法律的情况下生存下来，当时一群嬉皮士占领了一个废弃的军营，并建立了一个基于自我保护的反资本主义避风港。治理、自由思想和大麻合法化。</p><p> “我们需要真相时刻，”参与周二行动的一名居民说。 “我们已经从绿色能源、艺术、文化和 LGBTQ 权利的榜样，变成了我们所有的社区会议都在讨论 Pusher 街的暴力事件。”</p><p>克里斯蒂安尼亚早期的大麻贸易是由嬉皮士驾驶破旧的大众货车从亚洲运往哥本哈根推动的。如今，每年价值约 1.5 亿美元的大麻通过挤在 100 米长的鹅卵石步行街 Pusher 街的大约 30 个胶合板摊位流通。瑞典马尔默大学犯罪学副教授、克里斯蒂安尼亚问题专家 Kim Møller 表示，该行业约占丹麦大麻经济总量的三分之二，不过他补充说，没有人知道该业务的确切规模。</p><p>整个非洲大陆的大麻市场正在蓬勃发展。根据欧洲毒品和毒瘾监测中心的数据，2021 年，欧洲当局缉获了近 1,100 吨大麻脂和大麻草本，这是十年来的最高水平，这反映出其他更危险的麻醉品贸易的增加， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/police-raids-target-italian-mafia-across-europe-e4b5209d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">尤其是可卡因</a>。根据 EMCDDA 的数据，在过去的十年中，欧洲查获的大麻的效力也显着增加， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970203646004577213593506293770?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">长期成瘾的潜在危害也</a>随之增加。</p><p>贸易规模的不断扩大与克里斯蒂娜过去的生活格格不入。这个拥有约 850 名居民的社区坐落在丹麦首都一些最令人垂涎​​的房地产上，占地 34 公顷，距离议会大厦不到一英里。该公社禁止汽车通行，色彩缤纷、奇特的房屋、马厩和素食餐厅星罗棋布地分布在大湖泊周围，周围环绕着茂密的绿色植被。</p><p> Fleur Frilund, a 27-year-old copywriting student, moved into Christiania about six years ago, attracted to its proximity to nature and embrace of artists, freethinkers and old virtues such as craftsmanship, as many people built and renovated their own homes.</p><p> “It&#39;s a radically different way of living, compared to the big-city mentality just on the other side of the fence,” she said in an interview in her third-floor apartment, which previously belonged to a navy colonel.</p><p> It is this lifestyle that residents say they are trying to salvage. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/71c21a2b-c71b-4263-8d14-cdebb8974f18.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> On Sunday, two days before the operation, about a dozen activists met in a private home, behind drawn curtains, to complete their battle plan. Over coffee, the atmosphere was tense. Nobody touched the spread of hummus and freshly baked buns.</p><p> A middle-aged man&#39;s hands were visibly shaking. Many worried about retaliation from drug dealers in the days following the operation. One activist had sent his wife and children away for the week. In case of a confrontation during the operation, they agreed to only call the police if weapons appeared. One young activist proposed bringing along fire extinguishers in case the drug dealers set dogs on them.</p><p> In the end, the predawn operation ensured that no drug dealers confronted the activists—young and old, men and women—as they moved around Christiania, guiding the shipping containers into place in the dark. While younger participants trashed cannabis stalls, middle-age residents spray-painted the containers: “Pusher Street is closed.”</p><p> “Christianites have not turned against free cannabis,” an activist said. “But Pusher Street doesn&#39;t help the cause for free hash in any way. It&#39;s a worst-case scenario of what free cannabis can lead to.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831467?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A mural of a young Christiania resident who was killed in July in 2021. </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831462?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Emmerik Warburg has lived in Christiania since 1974.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Despite its anarchic origins, Christiania has maintained its own rules that banned cars, hard drugs, motorcycle gang insignia and bulletproof vests. In Pusher Street, photography is prohibited, as is running, so the drug dealers can tell when a police raid is under way.</p><p> Evicting residents from Christiania is nearly impossible. Some 40 to 50 residents are actively involved in the cannabis trade, according to Copenhagen police, and like other Christianites they have the right to veto any major decisions proposed in community meetings, and have protected Pusher Street.</p><p> Over the years, government pressure has forced Christiania to gradually relinquish some of its autonomy. In 2011, after seven years of failed negotiations with the state, residents agreed to purchase the land they lived on, formally legalizing their status as landowners. Unanimously refusing to buy property individually, they instead purchased it collectively through a fund for about $12 million, raising some of it through the sale of shares to the public.</p><p> “We are proof that poor people are also able to live in the center of the city,” said Emmerik Warburg, 70, who has lived in Christiania since 1974.</p><p> For decades, however, police raids have targeted Pusher Street, resulting in numerous deaths of residents and dealers. As the violence accompanying the trade worsened, police have continued to raid Pusher Street several times a week, often with brute force, only to see stalls re-erected and hidden hash re-emerge from hiding places as soon as they leave. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/87f5a147-79bd-4611-aaf8-073d5a2f4872.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> With criminal groups repeatedly clashing over Pusher Street, the freetown has become a battleground for Denmark&#39;s largest organized gangs. An influx of young outsiders has gradually pried control of the drug market from Christiania&#39;s own dealers.</p><p> Some gang members openly use hard drugs, carry weapons and employ minors, all of which contravene the commune&#39;s rules.</p><p> When a young man by a stall was shot and killed last year, following the killing of a young resident the year before, many were rattled.</p><p> “As long as we had our friends down there, we could keep up,” Warburg, who works for Christiania&#39;s self-governing administration, said about Pusher Street. “They violate the moral code of Christiania.”</p><p> Authorities and Christiania accuse each other of not doing enough to restore order, but have recently reached a rare agreement to potentially cooperate. At a meeting in June, residents agreed with the police, Justice Ministry and the city of Copenhagen—authorities that the group has been at loggerheads with for five decades—to set out an agreement to eventually clear Pusher Street.</p><p> “The violence and crime around Pusher Street have reached a level that we neither can nor want to accept,” said Lord Mayor of Copenhagen Sophie Hæstorp Andersen.</p><p> The activists didn&#39;t harbor illusions that Tuesday&#39;s action would permanently close down Pusher Street, but said they hoped it would serve as an invitation to the police and politicians to get serious about trying—even if it means the drug trade moves to other parts of Copenhagen, bringing violence in its wake. “It&#39;s a classic drug-crime dilemma: violence versus consumption,” said Møller, the criminologist. “You&#39;re damned if you do, damned if you don&#39;t.”</p><p> Write to Sune Engel Rasmussen at <a href="mailto:sune.rasmussen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sune.rasmussen@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831470?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Christiania in Copenhagen, as seen from the lakeside.</p></figcaption></figure></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:06:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-famous-hippie-freetown-is-ganging-up-on-drug-criminals-6f630367</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-famous-hippie-freetown-is-ganging-up-on-drug-criminals-6f630367<author><![CDATA[Sune Engel Rasmussen]]></author><category>休闲/艺术/酒店</category><category>旅游</category><category>Drug/Substance Use/Abuse</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>Drug Trafficking/Dealing</category><category> Gangs</category><category> Criminal Enterprises</category><category>社会问题</category><category>Trafficking/Smuggling</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> drug</category><category> substance use</category><category> abuse</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>drug trafficking</category><category> dealing</category><category> gangs</category><category> criminal enterprises</category><category>社会问题</category><category>trafficking</category><category> smuggling</category><category>闲暇</category><category>艺术</category><category>款待</category><category>旅游</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S.-Made Cluster Munitions Fuel Ukrainian Counteroffensive]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Bombs are destroying Russian trenches and artillery systems in an area where Kyiv&#39;s troops had struggled to advance <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117870"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831501?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A cluster-bomb carrier on the outskirts of Slovyansk, Ukraine.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Michal Burza/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117870"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ian-lovett" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ian Lovett</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name">Nikita Nikolaienko</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 8, 2023 7:23 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> ZAPORIZHZHIA, Ukraine—Newly delivered, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-send-cluster-munitions-to-bolster-ukraines-fight-against-dug-in-russians-d2dd292f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">American-made cluster munitions</a> have given fresh impetus to Ukraine&#39;s campaign to retake territory captured by Russia, after weeks of little progress.</p><p> Ukrainian soldiers say they have used the cluster bombs—which release dozens of smaller bomblets and can cause devastation over a broader area than ordinary artillery shells—to hit concentrations of Russian infantry, groups of vehicles and other targets, clearing the way for ground advances.</p><p> Kyiv&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-stalled-offensive-puts-biden-in-uneasy-political-position-6f686ab5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">counteroffensive operations have struggled</a> in the face of wide minefields and Moscow&#39;s superior air power, which have impeded large-scale efforts to use Western-supplied tanks and armored vehicles to reach and punch through lines of entrenched Russian forces.</p><p> While the cluster bombs alone won&#39;t tilt the battlefield balance of power decisively in Ukraine&#39;s favor, soldiers say they have helped them <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">retake Russian positions</a> that they had struggled to reach.</p><p> The munitions have been coupled with a change in tactics, which has allowed Ukrainian troops to advance to within striking distance of the main Russian defensive lines in some places. That progress has come with substantial casualties. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=EDA02BF5-0836-4277-AB7C-10442F70192F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> WSJ explains the technology behind cluster munitions and why they have raised humanitarian concerns. Illustration: Jacob Alexander Nelson<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>“The cluster bombs are good.他们是有效的，”侦察连连长阿纳托利·哈琴科上尉说。 “But the Russians are dug in deep, and they learn quickly.”</p><p> Kharchenko said Russian trenches can be 7 feet deep and that the Russians are adapting by spreading their troops more thinly to avoid heavy losses.</p><p> Recent fighting around the village of Robotyne, southeast of Zaporizhzhia city, has demonstrated the effectiveness of the new weapon in Ukraine&#39;s arsenal.</p><p> In late July, a platoon was pinned down east of the village, taking heavy Russian fire.该部队通过无线电向指挥官发出请求，要求撤退。他告诉排要躲起来。集束炸弹飞过头顶。 One soldier said he heard what sounded like rain, followed by chaos on Russian radio channels. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="1262" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/ad8ecb39-26bb-4a4d-b98b-c4700b367059-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> “They were yelling, &#39;We have lots of wounded.我们需要撤离。我们正在撤退，”乌克兰士兵说道。 The platoon moved forward to capture the Russian position, soldiers said.</p><p> Ukraine still hasn&#39;t reached the most formidable Russian defenses, a series of trenches, tank traps and other barriers. Military experts say Ukraine likely will need <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/german-made-leopard-tanks-for-ukraine-are-politically-symbolic-but-no-game-changer-11674151572?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">its Leopard 2 tanks</a> and other Western-provided armored vehicles to push through those lines.</p><p> To preserve those vehicles, which it was losing in numbers in minefields in early June, the Ukrainian military switched tactics. Now, infantry—bolstered by reserves called in from other units—are leading the advances through minefields on foot.</p><p> In concert with the strategic changes, soldiers said, Ukrainian forces now believe they have a chance for a breakthrough. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="2770" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/16d21f69-0148-4de6-8efa-d7313e2e8cf8-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Last week, as the 16-member platoon of Oleksandr, a 33-year-old infantry private, advanced toward a Russian position, it came under heavy fire from Russian machine guns. The Ukrainians were forced to retreat.</p><p> Then Ukraine hit the tree line hiding the Russian forces with cluster munitions.灌木丛和草着火了。 When the next assault began, Oleksandr could see the Russians he was firing at, who were no longer concealed in the scrub.</p><p> His platoon captured the position, killing about 12 Russians and taking several others captive. The prisoners had suffered concussions and burns from the cluster bombs, he said.</p><p> “With the cluster bombs, you fire three times and the trees totally collapse,” he said, adding that there was less incoming fire after the cluster attack. Because the munitions cause damage across a wide area, he said, they didn&#39;t need to be as accurate to be effective.</p><p> “Even if you miss a little, it still works,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831503?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Collected fragments of Russian rockets, including cluster rounds, that hit Kharkiv, Ukraine, last year.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Libkos/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Lt. Gen. Ben Hodges, a former commander of the US Army in Europe, said the US sent cluster munitions instead of more howitzer ammunition, which is <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-ramps-up-howitzer-shell-production-to-supply-ukraine-replenish-stockpiles-1e6dce54?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">running low in the West</a> .他预计集束炸弹会更有效。 They were designed for an army that was outnumbered, as Ukraine is now.</p><p> “Part of the way you deal with mass formations is with this scatterable munition,” he said. “If you&#39;re sitting in an open trench, you&#39;re going to pay a huge price due to these things.”</p><p> Videos posted recently on social media show Russian soldiers with half a dozen small wounds after Ukrainian cluster munition attacks. Hodges said the bombs also fit with what he saw as a shift in Ukrainian strategy to target Russian artillery pieces.</p><p> “These will really knock out artillery as long as they can reach it,” he said.</p><p> The weapons are banned by more than 100 countries, and the US decision to send them to Ukraine was heavily criticized by humanitarian groups. Not all the bomblets detonate right away, and they sometimes injure people who come upon them years later.</p><p> Russian forces have been using cluster munitions throughout the war: The white shell casings that carry them stick out of fields around the country. Ukraine also used them at times last year, according to a United Nations report. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="610" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/b0723491-abf8-41f3-aadf-419194652de4-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> A soldier in an artillery unit who has fired the cluster munitions said they were most effective in fields, where they dispersed over a wider area.</p><p> “Cluster munitions are important, but they&#39;re not a turning point,” he said, adding that it was important to have different kinds of artillery for different situations.</p><p> Usually, infantrymen said, artillery units fire a mix of different munitions at a Russian position before they advance on foot. Still, the human cost of the progress around Robotyne has been steep.</p><p> “We&#39;re demining the fields with bodies,” said a platoon commander from another of the newly formed, Western-trained brigades. “It&#39;s awful.”</p><p> Oleksandr Pershin, an infantryman, said that in the fields east of Robotyne, the ability of cluster munitions to wipe out tree cover was invaluable. During a recent assault on a Russian position, he said, there was no tree left above waist height.</p><p> “Everything else was destroyed,” he said, “mostly from the cluster munitions.”</p><p> Once his unit had taken that position, he said, they tried to keep pushing through the trees toward the next Russian line. For 24 hours, they made a series of assaults but kept getting pushed back, as the Russians sprayed them with machine-gun fire.</p><p> Eventually, they were ordered to dig trenches where they were.</p><p> While Pershin, 34, was digging, a rocket landed near him, spraying him with shrapnel and sending him to the hospital.当他说话时，他的手臂上吊着绷带，全身的伤口都缠着绷带。 Of 60 men in the assault, he said, 45 had been injured or killed. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=A74E51B6-FB53-4840-BB4D-2B1A0CCC986B&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> At least seven people were killed and over 80 injured in a Russian attack on the town of Pokrovsk on Monday, officials said. The strikes damaged apartments, a hotel, restaurants, shops and administrative buildings. Photo: Viacheslav Ratynskyi/Reuters<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p class="articleTagLine">—James Marson contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Ian Lovett at <a href="mailto:ian.lovett@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ian.lovett@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:23:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-made-cluster-munitions-fuel-ukrainian-counteroffensive-c45c305f<author><![CDATA[Ian Lovett]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>Armed Forces</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>armed forces</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S.-Made Cluster Munitions Fuel Ukrainian Counteroffensive]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Bombs are destroying Russian trenches and artillery systems in an area where Kyiv&#39;s troops had struggled to advance <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001117870"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
